column5: Hows the fishing there right now? Worth trying or not?
On a hike there a couple weeks ago I noticed that you'd have to walk about 30 yards through muck just to get to water that was 6"-12" deep. Water's edge was way out from shore.
Yellow perch, goldfish, white perch, sunfish, catfish, chubs and shiners, all small. Also some carp, trout, pike, bass, mostly small too.
Thanks Fishing. I'm gonna try it out tomorrow morning. I'll let you know what's going on.
I know that you have bass, pike, panfish, trout, drum, carp, bullheads, etc. kicking around there. Not sure what you'd catch right now though. maybe a trout?
I'll try Northern. Hope for the best. The ice will be here soon enough for some real fishing. Can't wait.
